time required: 35 minutes
---

Preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees (if you have a #toaster oven{}, skip this step).
Wash and dry all produce. Slice @corn on the cob{1} kernels off cob; discard cob.
Dice @roma tomato{1}(diced). Halve @ciabatta bread{1} (as if you were making a sandwich),
then halve each piece again on a diagonal. Zest and halve @lemon{1}(zested and halved).

In a #small bowl{}, combine @hot smoked paprika{1%teaspoon}, half the
@garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, and half the @celery salt{1%teaspoon}. Spread half the
spice mixture on a #plate{}; mix in @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, @salt{}, and
@pepper{}. To bowl with remaining spice mixture, stir in @sour cream{2%tablespoon},
@mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, lemon zest, @water{2%teaspoon}, a squeeze of lemon juice,
salt, and pepper. Set aside.

Place @crab cakes{10%ounce} on plate with panko mixture. Coat crab cakes all over
with panko, pressing to adhere. (It's OK if not all the panko sticks!)

Melt 1 TBSP @butter{3%tablespoon} in a large, preferably nonstick #pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add corn and cook, stirring, until charred, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> TIP: If corn begins to pop, cover pan.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #large bowl{}. Wipe out pan. Meanwhile, add 2 TBSP
butter to a second small bowl; microwave on high until melted, ~{30%seconds}. Stir
in remaining garlic powder, then brush onto cut sides of ciabatta. Season with
salt and pepper.

Heat a thin layer of @vegetable oil{} in pan used for corn over medium heat. Add
crab cakes and cook until golden brown and crispy, ~{4-5%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Lower heat if crab cakes begin to brown too quickly.

Meanwhile, toast ciabatta. To bowl with corn, add @mixed greens{2%ounce},
tomato, a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, and a squeeze of lemon juice
(to taste). Season with salt and pepper and toss to coat. Divide crab cakes,
salad, and garlic bread between plates. Drizzle crab cakes with sauce.